    <div class="details-2">
      <div class="about-time-cut">
        <div class="pic-time">
          <img
            class="pic-time-1"
            alt="image"
            src="../Assets/Images/book shop image (2).jpg"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="book-details">
          <h1 class="about-font">About Shop Booking Features</h1>
          <p class="book-details-1">
            Not only does a barbershop online booking system save your clients’
            time but it also saves the valuable time of your staff. They won’t
            need to spend so much time on the phone making appointments when
            they could do other more productive things for your barbershop
            instead. Think about how you can tune that staff member’s potential
            into something more compelling to them and to you. Keeping up to
            date is very important in an always-evolving world of business.The
            more time passes the more improvements become available to clients
            from your competitors and you have to take certain actions to not
            simply keep up with them but even move ahead and set trends. With
            each development customers become more demanding and pay attention
            to the smallest of details.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="about-time-cut">
        <div class="pic-time">
          <img
            class="pic-time-1"
            alt="image"
            src="../Assets/Images/book shop image (1).jpg"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="book-details">
          <h1 class="about-font">About Barber Booking Features</h1>
          <p class="book-details-1">
            When it comes to establishing a habit, it takes effort to make
            something into a routine, for example waking up early or going for a
            morning walk. By booking your barber appointment in advance you will
            know exactly which day and when your next appointment is, you can
            have it set for how many weeks out that you like, like 2 or 3 weeks.
            Many clients pre-book every 2 or 3 weeks to help them stay organized
            and ahead of their busy schedules by planning it. Taking these small
            but impactful steps to pre-book not only helps maintain the haircut
            at the right time before it gets too messy but also creates a
            routine of taking care of yourself. Some things in life can be
            skimped out on but when it comes to self-care it is important to
            remember to put yourself first and schedule a little “me” time to
            get your favorite barber services performed by your favorite barber
            at your favorite barbershop.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
